ready proved useful but have not yet been fully incorporated--public economics, development, law and economics, health, wage determination, and organizational economics. The result is an attempt to set the agenda of an important development in economics--an agenda that will interest policymakers, sociologists, and psychologists as well as economists. Contributors include Ian Ayres, B. Douglas Bernheim, Truman F. Bewley, Colin F. Camerer, Anne Case, Michael D. Cohen, Peter Diamond, Christoph Engel, Richard G. Frank, Jacob Glazer, Seppo Honkapohja, Christine Jolls, Botond Koszegi, Ulrike Malmendier, Sendhil Mullainathan, Antonio Rangel, Emmanuel Saez, Eldar Shafir, Sir Nicholas Stern, Jean Tirole, Hannu Vartiainen, and Timothy D. Wilson.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEconomicsxPsychological aspectsvCongresses. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / Theory.2bisacsh1 aBernheim, B. Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBewley, Truman F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamerer, Colin F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiamond, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiamond, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrank, Richard G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJolls, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalmendier, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRangel, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVartiainen, Hannu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVartiainen, Hannu, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook pack